  "body": "YP Appendix E defines that the input data must be zero padded.\n\nThe EC Recover precompiled contract takes 128 bytes as input, a concatenation of r, s, v EC sig values and a hash (message) that was signed.\n\nGo concatenates these values to create the input bytes, but does not pad them. This can cause the byte array to be less than 128 bytes, in which case the ecrecoverFunc returns nil as the input length is not correct.\n\nSee https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/core/vm/contracts.go#L69\n\nThis breaks consensus as a client correctly adding padding will accept e.g. s values small enough to have a big endian byte representation less than 32 bytes.\n",
